mypy: add stubs for buttplug core.messages

command: refactor to use protocols

- LinearCommand, RotateCommand, VibrateCommand define protocols for
  script commands that can be serialized into the respective buttplug
  types
- Serialization now uses the native type list/tuple combinations to be
  compatible with buttplug-py device.send_<type>_cmd() calls (instead of
  constructing the entire ButtplugMessage ourself)

- Suitable for use with Afesta/LPEG onarhythm scripts
script: add vorze vibrate script support
script: add vcsx onarhythm support
